     3	/// Frontend sink for non-TTY output.
     4	///
     5	/// The engine still drives all human-readable stdout via direct `println!`
     6	/// calls (so that byte-for-byte output is preserved). This sink therefore
     7	/// only reacts to `Message` events — which never originate from the current
     8	/// engine — and to terminal errors re-emitted through the channel. In
     9	/// practice that means it is a near no-op today and exists so that future
